%p Lesson Learned: Don't use em for font sizes. You'll get lost in the cascading effects.
%p REM is based on (root em). It fixes the em cascading problem. It's based on html font-sizing. So all you need to do is:
:plain
  html {
    font-size: 16px
    }

%p You can now use rems and they will be based off the font size 16 on your entire site! You can use REM units for fonts.
%p A good place to use ems is for padding buttons. Then the padding will increase based on the text size of the text in the button.
%p It's easy to build small, medium, and large buttons this way. Or you could manually scale the padding and margins as you need.
%p Use ems when you use media queries. It's beautiful..
